==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|vertu}} < {{etyl|fro}} {{term|vertu}} < {{etyl|la}} {{term|virtus||the qualities of a man, strength, courage, bravery, capacity, worth, manliness, applied to physical and intellectual excellence; also of moral excellence, virtue, morality}} < {{term|vir||man}}; see {{term|virile}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{enPR|vûrʹtū|vûrʹcho̅o̅}}, {{IPA|/ˈvɝ.tju/|/ˈvɝ.ʧu/}}
* {{audio|en-us-virtue.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|s|-}}

# {{uncountable}} excellence in morals
# {{countable}} A good habit
# {{countable}} a good model quality
# {{uncountable}} chastity and faithfulness
# {{countable}} an exemplary quality
